# A-series hardeners

### Application

A-series ester hardeners are designed for curing alkaline phenolic resins in the Alphaset process. They are used in cold-setting sand mixes for making moulds and cores from quartz and reclaimed sands.

## Key features and benefits

- Wide bench-life range – from a few minutes up to nearly one hour by selecting grades from A-2 to A-60.
- Universal use with all FS-series and other alkaline phenolic resins.
- Operation at shop temperature, without additional heating or cooling.
- No nitrogen- or sulphur-based acids – reduced gas defects and lower corrosion on equipment compared to acid systems.
- Simple dosing and mixing in standard cold-setting sand mixers.

